title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> be Galois, let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G=\mathop {\textrm {Gal}}\nolimits (\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F})]]></fr:tex>, and let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {L}=\Bbbk ^{H}]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H\leq  G]]></fr:tex>. Then (1) map
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\begin {split}\mathop {\textrm {Gal}}\nolimits (\Bbbk  / \mathbb {F})&\to \mathop {\textrm {Hom}}\nolimits _{\mathbb {F}}(\mathbb {L},\mathbb {K})\\ \sigma &\mapsto \sigma |_{\mathbb {L}}\end {split}]]></fr:tex>
is surjective and induces a bijection of sets
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[G/H\longleftrightarrow \mathop {\textrm {Hom}}\nolimits _{\mathbb {F}}(\mathbb {L},\Bbbk ).]]></fr:tex>
(2) Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {L} / \mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> is Galois if and only if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[H]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="gr-002P.xml"
addr="gr-002P"
title="Normal subgroup">normal</fr:link> (if and only if <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathop {\textrm {Hom}}\nolimits _{\mathbb {F}}(\mathbb {L},\Bbbk )=\mathop {\textrm {Aut}}\nolimits _{\mathbb {F}}(\mathbb {L})]]></fr:tex>). In that case, the above bijection is a group isomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[G/H\cong \mathop {\textrm {Gal}}\nolimits (\mathbb {L} / \mathbb {F})]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
